AN ANC member has received a letter asking him to resign from the North West legislature. While Daily Sun could not reach the member, who is said to be ill, the letter is signed by provincial party secretary and speaker Susan Dantjie. The letter informs Ndleleni Duma of a meeting held with the ANC and his family, and instructs him to resign. It says the party will pay his salary and medical aid until his term of office ends next year. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Some suspect the decision was made to reduce the number of ANC members who might vote against Premier Supra Mahumapelo in the open vote of no confidence against him today. A well-known ANC member and former MEC said the premier’s supporters were desperate to reduce the number of members who could vote with the oppositionThe EFF’s Alfred Motsi said: “We specifically demanded secret voting to protect ourselves. “ANC MPLs have a vigilante group known as Fearvokol which intimidates political opponents.” The SunTeam sent emails and SMSes to provincial ANC spokesman Gerald Modise but he was not available for comment.